# AI Text Intelligence Web — New Full-Stack Project

Build a brand new project at `d:\NLP project\ai-text-intelligence-web\` using the **same NLP concepts** as the existing Streamlit project, but with a modern HTML/CSS/JS frontend + Flask API backend.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `ai-text-intelligence` project will NOT be touched.

## Proposed Architecture

```
ai-text-intelligence-web/
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py                  ← Flask API server
│   ├── requirements.txt        ← Python dependencies
│   ├── modules/
│   │   ├── song_interpreter.py ← Song meaning analysis (same logic)
│   │   ├── poetry_meter.py     ← Poetry meter checker (same logic)
│   │   └── summarizer.py       ← Text summarizer (same logic, no Streamlit)
│   └── utils/
│       └── preprocessing.py    ← Text preprocessing (same logic)
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html              ← Main page
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css           ← All styling (dark theme, glassmorphism, animations)
│   └── js/
│       └── app.js              ← Frontend logic (API calls, DOM manipulation)
└── README.md
```

## Proposed Changes

---

### Backend (Flask API)

#### [NEW] `backend/app.py`
- Flask server with 3 API endpoints:
  - `POST /api/interpret` → Song meaning interpreter
  - `POST /api/meter` → Poetry meter checker
  - `POST /api/summarize` → Text summarizer
- CORS enabled for frontend communication
- JSON request/response format

#### [NEW] `backend/modules/song_interpreter.py`
- Same logic as existing: VADER sentiment + keyword theme detection
- No Streamlit dependency

#### [NEW] `backend/modules/poetry_meter.py` 
- Same logic as existing: CMU dict stress analysis, meter detection, rhyme scheme
- No Streamlit dependency

#### [NEW] `backend/modules/summarizer.py`
- Same logic as existing: DistilBART model for summarization  
- **Removed `@st.cache_resource`** → replaced with a simple module-level singleton

#### [NEW] `backend/utils/preprocessing.py`
- Identical to existing: clean → tokenize → remove stopwords pipeline

#### [NEW] `backend/requirements.txt`
- flask, flask-cors, nltk, transformers, torch

---

### Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS)

#### [NEW] `frontend/index.html`
- Single-page app with 3 navigation tabs (Song, Poetry, Summarize)
- Semantic HTML5 structure
- Google Fonts (Inter)

#### [NEW] `frontend/css/style.css`
- Dark theme with purple/blue gradient accents
- Glassmorphism cards
- Smooth micro-animations (hover effects, loading spinners, fade-ins)
- Fully responsive layout
- Keyword badges, result cards matching existing design aesthetic

#### [NEW] `frontend/js/app.js`
- Tab switching logic
- `fetch()` calls to Flask API endpoints
- Loading states, error handling
- Dynamic DOM rendering of results (emotion, theme, stress patterns, summary)

---

### Documentation

#### [NEW] `README.md`
- Project overview, setup instructions, API documentation

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Text Summarizer uses a large AI model (~1.2GB download).** The DistilBART model will be downloaded on first use. This is the same behavior as your existing project. Should I keep it, or would you prefer to skip the summarizer in this new project?

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Start Flask backend: `python backend/app.py`
2. Open `frontend/index.html` in browser
3. Test all 3 features with sample inputs
4. Verify responsive design at different screen sizes
